    The `dep3changelog` command is used to generate changelog files from DEB3 (Debian Enhancement Proposal 3) formatted information.  This helps create a standard and readable history of changes for a project.  Simply put, it takes change information from DEB3 formatted data and creates a changelog file detailing what has changed in a new version.

